This post goes out to my warrior of a grandmother. Ever since the day I was born, it was clear there was a special bond between the two of us. Growing up we would shop til we drop, talk about boys, and of course, exchange jewelry. A few years ago, we thought we were going to lose her a few times due to multiple forms of cancer, but she fought hard and became a survivor. Then Alzheimer’s came into our lives and rocked our worlds. Without hesitation, my mom immediately stepped up to the plate and has been a rockstar. There are truly not enough characters in this caption to explain how much my mom has done to care for her mom… and really, our entire family during this emotional time. Unfortunately, this disease is not controlled so when it progressed to the point of needing advanced care, my grandma needed to move into an Alzheimer’s memory care center. I knew my grandma would be scared, and I didn’t know how long I’d be lucky enough to fly home to visit her, so I jumped onto a plane straight from Vegas Labor Day Weekend, and spent the first 4 days of her new stay by her side. During my time, I saw her at her best and at her worst. I don’t know what tomorrow will bring, but I do know I’ll cherish these memories captured in these few photographs for the rest of my life. 

My mom will be walking in honor of my grandma at the Walk to End Alz in Tampa later this year. If you’d like to make a donation, even just $1, to help scientists try to find a cure for this disease, please DM me. My whole family humbly thanks you 💜
